        {
          "_params": {
            "showMeta": false
          },
          "title": "DATASET",
          "meta": "By John Smith posted July 30, 2015",
          "_tags": [
            "Theme"
          ],
          "_name": "header3",
          "_anchor": "header3-n"
        },
        {
          "text": "<p>The current database includes U.S. presidents' inaugural speeches and the State of the States Addresses (governors' new year speeches) in 2019. The governors' speech data are downloaded from the &nbsp;<a href=\"https://fivethirtyeight.com/features/what-americas-governors-are-talking-about/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">What America’s Governors Are Talking About</a>&nbsp;project (see&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/fivethirtyeight/data/tree/master/state-of-the-state\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Github)</a>&nbsp;by the group FiveThirtyEight. Inaugural speeches are downloaded from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The American Presidency Project</a>&nbsp;hosted by UCSB.&nbsp;</p>",
          "_tags": [
            "Theme"
          ],
          "_name": "content1",
          "_anchor": "content1-o"
        },
        {
          "_params": {
            "showMeta": false
          },
          "title": "METHODOLOGY",
          "meta": "By John Smith posted July 30, 2015",
          "_tags": [
            "Theme"
          ],
          "_name": "header3",
          "_anchor": "header3-1q"
        },
        {
          "text": "<p>Corpus linguistic programs Lancsbox developed by Lancaster University is used to analyze the normalized frequencies of the promise-expressions and to generate the concordances. Since many modals can express multiple modalities (e.g. <i>must </i>as a epistemic/possibility modal and a deontic/obligation modal), annotations to distinguish these functions are yet to be added.&nbsp;</p><p>\n</p><div>\n</div><div>The concordance lines extracted are then further analyzed with TopicModelingTool. Note this is not the main focus on this project and the topic modeling process is very preliminary. However, the current result might provide us a glimpse of the content of promises made by different presidents and governors.</div><p></p>",
          "_tags": [
            "Theme"
          ],
          "_name": "content1",
          "_anchor": "content1-28"
        },
        {
          "_params": {
            "showMeta": false
          },
          "title": "VISUALIZATION",
          "meta": "By John Smith posted July 30, 2015",
          "_tags": [
            "Theme"
          ],
          "_name": "header3",
          "_anchor": "header3-1e"
        },
        {
          "text": "<p>Visualization is realized through Fourish. Frequencies of different expressions are visualized with Grif of column charts, stacked area charts, stacked bar charts, map. For governors' promise section, an interactive map of U.S. is created to show main topics of promises made by governors across the country and the frequencies of promise-expressions identified in the current project. The current version of the website only show pictures of visualizations with external links to the Flourish pages.<br></p>",
          "_tags": [
            "Theme"
          ],
          "_name": "content1",
          "_anchor": "content1-1d"
        },
