          "title": "Inaugual speeches",
          "text": "The first inaugural speech was given by George Washington in 1865; the most recent one was by Trump in 2017.&nbsp;<br><br>Did presidents make promises in these inaugural speeches out of obligation or volition? Is there a generally more preferred category of expressions to make promises in inaugural speeches? Are there any changes of the presidnets' preferences over time?&nbsp;<br>",
          "buttons": "<a data-app-btn=\"true\" class=\"mbr-buttons__btn btn btn-lg btn-danger animated fadeInUp delay\" href=\"https://mobirise.com\" data-toolbar=\"-mbrBtnMove\">DOWNLOAD NOW</a> ",
